<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8666&amp;p=90764#p90764"><![CDATA[
I'm into homebrew because I've had an interest in game dev ever since I started programming. I'm attracted to the NES specifically (and retro systems generally) because it's possible for one developer or a small team to actually produce a finished game that's on the same level as commercial releases. On modern consoles and the PC that's hardly possible anymore.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3412">Karatorian</a> — Thu Mar 01, 2012 7:18 am</p><hr />
